    • setLengths

      public void setLengths(int length1, int length2, ReaderMemory readerMemory)
      Sets the valid code lengths To allow One Discrete Length, LengthOne should be greater than zero and LengthTwo equal zero. To allow Two Discrete Lengths, LengthOne should be greater LengthTwo. To allow Length Within Range, LengthOne should be less than LengthTwo. To allow Any Length, LengthOne and LengthTwo should both be zero.
      Parameters:
      length1 - Length 1 value
      length2 - Length 2 value
      readerMemory - Permanent or Temporary
